article.description: Tilman Dunbar had 20 points and six assists, Shawn Anderson added 18 points and Navy beat Loyola (Md.) 71-51 Wednesday night for the Midshipmen's second straight season sweep of the Greyhounds.
article.headline: Navy sweeps season series with Loyola (Md.), 71-51
article.linkText: Navy sweeps season series with Loyola (Md.), 71-51
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Tilman Dunbar had 20 points and six assists, Shawn Anderson added 18 points and Navy beat Loyola (Md.) 71-51 Wednesday night for the Midshipmen's second straight season sweep of the Greyhounds. Navy improved to 10-2 on the road to set a program record for most road wins in a season. Will Kelly added 14 points, five rebounds, four assists and four blocks for Navy (17-9, 8-5 Patriot), which matched last season's conference win total with five games to go. Dunbar has scored in double figures in six straight games -- the longest streak of his four-year career. Jarred Jones and Andre Walker had eight points apiece for Loyola (8-16, 7-6), which was held to 15-of-45 shooting (33 percent). Loyola trailed 35-19 at halftime after Jace Hogan hit a shot just before the buzzer.
